# install Eclipse 

Navagate to eclipse.org 

Click install 64-bit version

Download the file

Open file explorer

Double click the file

Drag the eclipse installer file to the desktop

double click the icon on the desktop

right click eclipse-inst and select run

Select the Eclipse IDE for Java EE Developers (best for the spring framework)

click the hamburger menu and select advanced options

select eclipse IDE for Java EE Developers  64-Bit
Product version Photon
Select next
Dont select any tools, and press next again.

create a folder called software and use that to install eclipse

rename the folder eclipse and not eclipse-photon

delete the installer folder



